  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This pilot study is planned to validate the comparability of HbA1c results obtained from
      whole blood collection via venous phlebotomy versus a capillary collection of whole blood.
      The participant will self-collect capillary blood into HbA1c prep vials containing a buffer;
      these prep vials will be sent to the CBL at ambient temperature via US Postal System (USPS)
      mail. The feasibility of self-collection of these capillary samples by GRADE participants
      will also be evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
